message.content: Based on the filescan output, a possible payload of the initial exploit affecting the victim's bank account could be the file "sdra64.exe" located in \Device\HarddiskVolume1\WINDOWS\system32\. This file appears to have been accessed and could potentially be a malicious executable responsible for the unusual activity in the victim's bank account. Further analysis of this file, its behavior, and any related artifacts would be necessary to confirm its role in the incident.
